summary: The class is a runtime validated representation of an actual command argument and its value passed by a user or an application.
remarks:
An argument id is always unique within a command. By design implements the default equality and using property. Thus, two arguments with the same id are equal irrespective of other property values. This is done to improve performance during lookup and avoid multiple arguments with same identifiers.

The arguments can have same ids across multiple commands. Each has collection that contains attributes with unique ids.
